Shorten Package Install Time in Scratch Orgs by Skipping a Handler

To shorten package install time when installing in scratch orgs, you can specify the FeatureEnforcement skip handler when using either the PackageInstallRequest object, or the sf package install command.

Where: This change applies to unlocked packages, second-generation managed packages, and first-generation managed packages installed in scratch orgs.

How: Set the SkipHandler field on the PackageInstallRequest object to FeatureEnforcement. Or use the CLI and specify:

sf package install --skip-handlers FeatureEnforcement
title: Shorten Package Install Time in Scratch Orgs
